  "description": [
    "EDITORIAL COMMENT f 5 By the time The Advocate Efforts for Psace reaches its readers the ques tion of peace or continued butchery called war will probably have been settled The outlook at present is gloomy The President has made every effort consistent with the delicacy of the position which he occupies toward the two negotiat ing parties The question now hinges on the cession to the Japanese of Saghalienwhich is now in their possessionand the payment by Russia of an indem nity sufficient to cover the cost to Japan of the war Russia would likely yield the island but protests against the payment of an indemnity to any amount or under any name She cites the absence of prece dents and claims that such payment would bring to her dishonor and loss of prestige We believe that if Japan really wishes peace the time has come for mag nanimity on her part Concession made to the just pride of a conquered and sadly beset people would in the end bring the twofold blessing that marks the quality of mercy The world not Russia alone would be the gainer and Japan herself would not long feel financial straim The prestige"
  ],
